WEBVTT

00:15.898 --> 00:20.398
They're going in!
Wait for me, for fuck's sake!

00:22.148 --> 00:26.357
Come on, for fuck's sake.
You're so slow! Hop on.

00:28.857 --> 00:33.982
They're betting 1200 on
who jumps in the lake first.

00:34.107 --> 00:38.982
Come on. It's so cold.

00:40.232 --> 00:43.440
Wait for me, for fuck's sake!

00:45.773 --> 00:50.482
- Go. Jump in!
- No, I don't want to.

00:54.857 --> 00:57.440
It's freezing.

01:15.232 --> 01:17.607
Shit, I have a cramp.

01:19.773 --> 01:23.107
- Fucking hell!
- Coming!

01:34.482 --> 01:38.815
Put him in the recovery position.

01:38.940 --> 01:41.357
Pump his chest a little.

01:41.482 --> 01:44.107
Don't fuck him up!

01:46.440 --> 01:51.482
- Did you check the eel traps?
- I want 600. I came second.

01:51.607 --> 01:54.648
There's hot toddy in the car.
Come on, boys.

02:12.148 --> 02:17.357
THE HUNT

03:07.357 --> 03:09.982
Something fishy's going on here.

03:12.232 --> 03:15.607
Oh, it's you, Pelle!
Are you alone?

03:17.857 --> 03:21.773
- Get him! Get him!
- You're too many!

03:23.482 --> 03:27.523
Watch out! I'm dangerous.
This is my new weapon, Pelle.

03:31.565 --> 03:36.523
- Hang up your clothes.
- I have to go number two.

03:36.648 --> 03:40.023
Lucas can help you, then.

03:40.148 --> 03:45.315
Would you please help him?
All his clothes come off.

03:45.440 --> 03:47.815
Is jumping such a great idea?

03:59.273 --> 04:03.440
- I'm done.
- Can you handle it yourself?

04:03.565 --> 04:09.190
- Hello! Wipe.
- Hey, watch your tone.

04:09.315 --> 04:12.440
Come here.

04:12.565 --> 04:15.190
And soap.

04:16.940 --> 04:19.690
Come on.

04:22.315 --> 04:26.190
Hi, Klara. Something wrong?

04:26.315 --> 04:31.190
- I'm lost.
- Oh. Where's Mum and Dad?

04:31.315 --> 04:35.773
At home.
I forgot to look where I was going.

04:35.898 --> 04:39.523
All of a sudden I was here.

04:39.648 --> 04:45.982
You still can't step on the lines?
So you don't know where you're going?

04:46.107 --> 04:51.190
- No, and I don't remember the way.
- That's a shame.

04:53.607 --> 04:56.898
I remember the way.
Why don't we go together?

04:59.065 --> 05:01.107
I'll look up
while you look at the lines?

05:01.232 --> 05:05.773
I'd like that.
ls Fanny coming too?

05:05.898 --> 05:09.690
- Yes, she's coming too.
- Good. She'll watch out for us.

05:13.065 --> 05:18.440
- What's your favourite dish?
- Probably venison.

05:18.565 --> 05:24.107
Mine's fish fingers.
Why do you work in our nursery?

05:24.232 --> 05:30.482
Well, I was a teacher at your
brother's school, but then it closed.

05:32.398 --> 05:37.523
My dad says you're sad because
you live alone in a big house.

05:37.648 --> 05:39.690
Does he now?

05:39.815 --> 05:44.440
Keep your head high
and your feet on the ground.

05:44.565 --> 05:47.940
If you are still sulking,
you can get a kick up the arse.

05:51.648 --> 05:55.773
- Did your dad teach you that?
- You can get a kick up the arse.

05:55.898 --> 06:01.898
- Can I come and walk Fanny?
- As often as you like.

06:02.023 --> 06:05.065
Try calling her.

06:05.190 --> 06:08.398
- Fanny!
- Louder.

06:08.523 --> 06:12.440
Fanny! Come here!

06:12.565 --> 06:17.648
- Klara, where have you been?
- At the supermarket.

06:17.773 --> 06:23.107
Sweetie. Haven't I told you
not to run away from home?

06:23.273 --> 06:27.273
- You want coffee?
- Fanny, come.

06:27.440 --> 06:31.523
- Go to your room.
- Shit!

06:31.648 --> 06:35.982
- Look what I found in the gutter.
- Hi, Lucas.

06:36.107 --> 06:38.773
Hi, Fanny.
Who's a good girl?

06:39.940 --> 06:45.190
Hi, babe. You didn't put that thing
away like you promised.

06:45.315 --> 06:48.190
Do you also leave
your sporting gun lying about?

06:49.815 --> 06:54.357
I've told you, it's a rifle.
It's not a sport.

06:54.523 --> 06:57.107
- Torsten!
- Torsten!

06:59.232 --> 07:01.815
Young lady,
you have some thinking to do.

07:01.898 --> 07:05.232
We're off to buy football boots.

07:05.357 --> 07:08.982
Don't touch the pie! I mean it!

07:09.107 --> 07:11.732
It better be in one piece.
Torsten, are you coming?

07:14.065 --> 07:19.190
Drop in one of these days.
We'll make lasagne.

07:19.315 --> 07:20.898
Lasagneâ€œ.

07:29.107 --> 07:35.190
She'll be furious.
Like that. I got it.

07:35.315 --> 07:38.565
How are things
with Marcus and your ex?

07:38.690 --> 07:40.482
Everything's fine.

07:43.648 --> 07:49.815
I can tell when you're lying.
Your eye twitches.

07:49.940 --> 07:53.732
- Really?
- Don't lie to me, Lucas.

07:55.273 --> 07:59.190
She'll only let me see him
every other weekend.

07:59.315 --> 08:02.232
Call Kirsten.

08:02.357 --> 08:07.315
Forget the lawyers.
Quiet, Fanny!

08:07.440 --> 08:11.940
Then don't mention Kirsten.
Stop it, Fanny!

08:12.065 --> 08:18.190
- Do you miss Marcus?
- Of course I miss my boy.

08:18.315 --> 08:22.565
- Pick up the phone and call Kirsten.
- Stop!

08:22.690 --> 08:26.982
- Down, stupid dog!
- Stop it.

08:27.107 --> 08:29.232
Shame on you!

08:30.565 --> 08:36.148
He's unhappy that it's twelve days
at your place and two at mine.

08:36.273 --> 08:39.565
<i>I think it works fine.</i>

08:39.732 --> 08:42.898
Can I say something?
Thank you.

08:43.023 --> 08:46.398
He wants to spend
more time here.

08:46.523 --> 08:50.065
He said that
you were okay with it.

08:50.190 --> 08:52.523
Isn't that true?

08:52.648 --> 08:57.815
<i>Lucas, what else could he say?
He feels sorry for you.</i>

08:57.940 --> 09:02.898
- Come again? He feels sorry for me?
- <i>Of</i> course!

09:03.023 --> 09:07.607
- Please behave like an adult.
- You <i>have</i> to sez' yourself aside.

09:07.732 --> 09:12.232
I do, damn it!
He was the one who asked.

09:12.357 --> 09:17.315
<i>You can't even keep an agreement.
You're not supposed to call me.</i>

09:18.273 --> 09:23.482
When are we supposed to talk,
if you don't call, and I can't call?

09:23.565 --> 09:25.690
When can we talk then?

09:26.607 --> 09:31.857
- I'm <i>hanging</i> up.
- No. When can we talk? Kirsten?

09:57.315 --> 10:01.148
Old rod, big rod, crooked rod,
wrinkly rod...

10:01.273 --> 10:04.565
- Rod, rod, rod!
- Hi, Klara.

10:04.690 --> 10:07.773
Look, Klara.
A giant stiff rod.

10:07.898 --> 10:13.232
- Let's go to my room.
- Massive hooker rod!

10:21.440 --> 10:25.648
- Good morning, Klara.
- Good morning.

10:25.773 --> 10:32.648
<i>- Listen, you have to take her.
- You never keep an agreement!</i>

10:32.773 --> 10:34.232
<i>We don't have an agreement!</i>

10:34.357 --> 10:38.565
Are they arguing? Are you sad?

10:38.690 --> 10:42.440
No, he can have
a kick up the arse.

10:42.565 --> 10:47.982
<i>If you have children,
you must take them to nursery!</i>

10:48.107 --> 10:53.815
- Shall I take you to nursery?
- I'd like that.

10:53.940 --> 10:57.023
I'll let your clad know.

10:57.148 --> 11:01.398
<i>- Hi. You're making a racket.
- We can'! find Klara.</i>

11:01.523 --> 11:06.232
- She's here. Why don't I take her?
- Yes, of course. Bye.

11:07.440 --> 11:09.940
It's okay. Let's go.

11:12.898 --> 11:17.732
You can look where we're going,
then I'll look out for lines.

12:02.773 --> 12:07.023
You're so weak!

12:07.107 --> 12:11.482
Who wants to fly?

12:13.273 --> 12:15.857
- Me too!
- Come here, then.

12:19.190 --> 12:22.732
I need a break. I'm dying here.

12:22.857 --> 12:26.607
- Me too!
- Me too!

12:26.732 --> 12:30.732
- He's dying.
- Yeah!

12:31.898 --> 12:36.857
- Wake up!
- Come on, wake up!

12:36.982 --> 12:40.440
Who's waking the dead?

12:40.565 --> 12:43.565
Here's the hand of death.

12:47.273 --> 12:49.565
Time for fruit.

12:52.107 --> 12:58.315
We'll be right there.
Clean up first. Klara...

13:01.565 --> 13:05.565
I found a small present
in my coat pocket.

13:10.315 --> 13:14.148
I think you should give it
to one of the boys.

13:16.940 --> 13:22.690
- It's not from me.
- But it says "Klara".

13:24.440 --> 13:28.023
Then someone must be teasing you.

13:30.190 --> 13:35.148
Why don't you give it to your mum
or the person who made it?

13:35.273 --> 13:38.857
And kissing on the lips
is only for Mum and Dad.

13:40.482 --> 13:43.898
It's not from me.
You're lying.

13:46.190 --> 13:50.440
- It's not from me.
- Klara?

13:52.107 --> 13:55.773
Boys. Tidy up.
And wash your hands.

13:55.898 --> 14:00.482
- Are you serious?
- Yes, I am.

14:02.065 --> 14:06.107
Hi, Pelle and Janus.

14:13.898 --> 14:19.315
Hi, sweetie. Are you still here?
Your mum will be here in a minute.

14:21.648 --> 14:23.898
Excited about Christmas?

14:25.690 --> 14:30.690
Do you remember the carol?
Let's sing it.

14:40.773 --> 14:44.065
I hate Lucas.

14:44.190 --> 14:47.857
- I thought you were friends.
- We're not.

14:48.940 --> 14:50.565
Why not?

14:52.065 --> 14:56.232
He's stupid, and he's ugly.

14:57.857 --> 15:02.773
- And he has a willie.
- Most men do.

15:03.232 --> 15:05.690
So does your dad and Torsten.

15:09.398 --> 15:16.690
Yes, but his is pointing
straight out. Like a rod.

15:19.315 --> 15:23.523
- Why do you say that?
- Because it does.

15:27.398 --> 15:29.107
Did something happen, Klara?

15:31.648 --> 15:35.898
He gave me this heart,
but I don't want it.

15:38.982 --> 15:43.690
That's no good.
Then throw it away.

15:45.940 --> 15:49.107
Is Santa coming this year?

15:49.232 --> 15:53.440
Yeah... You never know.

15:53.565 --> 15:59.315
- I think he will.
- If you've been nice, he will.

15:59.440 --> 16:05.565
Hi, Grethe. Hi, sweetheart.
Are you sitting in the dark?

16:05.648 --> 16:12.065
I'm so sorry.
I came as fast as I could.

16:13.107 --> 16:18.523
Did you have fun?
Something on your mind?

16:18.648 --> 16:23.523
No, we've collected mushrooms
and turds in the woods today.

16:23.648 --> 16:27.815
Sounds nice!
Come on. Let's go home.

16:27.940 --> 16:32.315
- See you, Klara.
- Bye, Grethe.

16:33.732 --> 16:35.940
Come, sweetie.

16:37.107 --> 16:41.482
Let's hurry home and make dinner.

16:51.690 --> 16:58.065
Okay. Wow.
I'm thrilled to hear that.

16:58.190 --> 17:03.315
- Did something happen?
- Bye-bye, see you!

17:03.440 --> 17:09.190
- <i>Did you</i> talk about <i>it?</i>
- <i>Yes. He wants to live with you.</i>

17:09.315 --> 17:13.815
- <i>He's</i> very angry.
- It'll be perfect.

17:13.940 --> 17:17.357
I'll take him to yours
as often as he wants.

17:18.857 --> 17:20.897
Are you okay?

17:22.107 --> 17:25.982
<i>You'd better talk to him.
I'll go get him.</i>

17:27.022 --> 17:30.607
Sorry. I'll just go through here.

17:30.732 --> 17:36.440
<i>Dad? It's great. But I can't
change schools before Christmas.</i>

17:36.565 --> 17:40.648
- We'll <i>manage.</i>
<i>- I'd better go and see to Mum.</i>

17:40.773 --> 17:46.065
Okay. And Marcus,
be nice to her. It's not easy.

17:46.190 --> 17:50.857
<i>- Of</i> course. <i>Bye.</i>
- I love you. See you soon.

17:56.815 --> 17:59.648
- Sorry. Hi.

18:01.732 --> 18:06.315
That was my son.
He's going to live with me now.

18:13.398 --> 18:14.940
Coffee...

18:17.107 --> 18:19.315
Coffee now? Here?

18:19.440 --> 18:20.898
Yes.

18:22.232 --> 18:26.065
Let's have some coffee.
You want milk?

18:26.190 --> 18:29.232
No. I want it black and strong.

18:42.690 --> 18:48.065
<i>You're supposed to be gentle, right?
Do the dishes.</i>

19:01.273 --> 19:04.440
Just like this?

19:14.273 --> 19:16.273
Thank you.

19:23.565 --> 19:27.398
- Will you clean up the playground?
- Sure.

19:53.565 --> 19:56.648
- See you tomorrow.
- Monday.

19:57.857 --> 20:01.607
- Tomorrow.
- No, on Monday. It's weekend.

20:05.690 --> 20:09.315
I like it when we can see each other.

20:12.357 --> 20:14.440
Me too.

20:17.482 --> 20:19.648
Come here.

20:20.857 --> 20:22.607
You're sweet.

20:27.232 --> 20:28.940
You too.

21:48.398 --> 21:52.357
Let's put it here.

21:52.482 --> 21:55.357
You can't even hit the sack.

21:55.482 --> 21:59.898
It's the first time
I didn't shoot anything.

22:00.023 --> 22:03.190
It really is.

22:03.315 --> 22:09.023
Perhaps it's your eyes.
You might want to try these.

22:20.107 --> 22:24.523
Listen. I'll call Ulla.

22:24.648 --> 22:28.898
You bring roast pork.
Eel. Black pudding.

22:29.023 --> 22:33.107
- Johan! Apple pork.
- Let's just say cheers.

22:33.232 --> 22:36.107
You'll bring apple pork.

22:37.482 --> 22:40.065
Hello. It's Lucas. Hello?

22:47.107 --> 22:52.148
I can't hear a thing. One moment.
Hello, Lucas here.

23:28.857 --> 23:30.023
It's me.

23:49.773 --> 23:51.898
<i>Pussy! Pussy!</i>

24:00.482 --> 24:03.398
I've been thinking about you a lot.

24:16.648 --> 24:22.023
- Who did you call? A bird?
- Bent, stop it!

24:22.148 --> 24:26.607
Hey, I'm quietly trying to tell you,

24:26.732 --> 24:30.107
that he made a phone call
to a lady!

24:34.565 --> 24:42.857
<i>Would Lucas, would Lucas,
would Lucas drink a beer?</i>

24:52.815 --> 24:56.148
<i>Oh surely, oh surely,
oh surely he would!</i>

24:56.273 --> 24:59.857
<i>Oh surely, oh surely,
oh surely he would.</i>

25:03.232 --> 25:08.732
- I brought a present.
- And it's not even Christmas.

25:08.857 --> 25:11.732
Come on. I'll help you.

25:11.857 --> 25:16.398
- How much did he drink?
- I don't know. Lost count.

25:16.523 --> 25:22.607
- Thank you so much.
- Lucas...

25:22.732 --> 25:28.065
You're my best friend.

25:28.148 --> 25:34.315
- See you. Have you got him?
- Kisses.

25:36.023 --> 25:40.148
I'll call if I need you.
Goodbye.

25:41.398 --> 25:44.523
Agnes...

25:47.065 --> 25:52.273
I need to tell you something.
Do you know why you're so pretty?

25:52.398 --> 25:57.273
- No.
- Because you don't know.

26:02.815 --> 26:07.482
- Oh, honey.
- I love you.

26:12.482 --> 26:15.565
I love you.

26:17.148 --> 26:19.232
I love you. A lot.

26:45.982 --> 26:48.523
Fanny. Fanny.

26:48.648 --> 26:50.690
Fanny, where are you?

26:52.648 --> 26:56.982
Come here. Come!
Thank you for the ball.

28:40.023 --> 28:42.732
I got you! First time ever!
Got you!

28:52.940 --> 28:56.690
- Lucas. Lucas!
- Hi.

28:56.815 --> 29:00.565
- You can't escape me.
- Do you have a minute?

29:00.648 --> 29:04.815
Yeah, just a second.
Boys, I can't catch you.

29:04.940 --> 29:08.898
After I drink some superjuice,
I'll be back.

29:10.982 --> 29:15.857
- Hi, Grethe.
- Please take a seat.

29:15.982 --> 29:21.398
- How's little Marcus?
- Good. He's not so little anymore.

29:22.482 --> 29:26.315
He's planning to move in
with me before Christmas.

29:28.690 --> 29:33.690
I've been racking my brain,
but I can't get it out of my head.

29:37.023 --> 29:42.440
A child has told me something,
I need to talk to you about it.

29:44.773 --> 29:49.857
This child has a vivid imagination,
but I still wanted to mention it.

29:49.982 --> 29:52.482
Sure.
Who are we talking about?

29:54.732 --> 29:56.690
I can't tell you.

30:03.065 --> 30:08.607
The child says things have happened.
Things meant for adults only.

30:12.148 --> 30:15.148
What things?
What has happened?

30:15.273 --> 30:20.107
The child says that
he or she doesn't like you.

30:21.523 --> 30:27.898
And that he or she has seen
your private parts...

30:38.357 --> 30:42.107
How the hell would that
even be possible?

30:42.232 --> 30:43.857
I don't know.

30:50.398 --> 30:51.815
Shit...

30:55.482 --> 30:59.232
It doesn't sound good,
but don't worry.

31:00.190 --> 31:03.523
I'm not jumping to conclusions.
We'll work it out.

31:05.482 --> 31:10.357
- What exactly has been said?
- I can't tell you.

31:12.607 --> 31:17.023
And it's time for fruit
so we'd better move on.

31:20.773 --> 31:25.982
You should take a few days off.
Then we'll sort this out.

31:26.107 --> 31:30.023
Finish your shift today,
and then we'll think of something.

31:30.148 --> 31:32.148
I'll do that.

32:08.857 --> 32:12.273
- Did I keep you waiting?
- No, it's fine.

32:12.398 --> 32:16.273
I'm not sure how this works.

32:17.815 --> 32:20.482
Let's just get started.

32:22.690 --> 32:25.232
Yes, Klara...

32:26.898 --> 32:32.773
Can you try to tell me exactly
what you told Grethe?

32:48.315 --> 32:53.232
Please tell him
what you said about the heart.

33:01.065 --> 33:03.315
I didn't say anything.

33:05.065 --> 33:10.982
Is Grethe just making this up?

33:11.857 --> 33:15.023
Or did you make it up?

33:15.148 --> 33:16.815
No.

33:17.732 --> 33:21.565
Alright...
Then try telling me.

33:29.315 --> 33:32.232
It's okay to tell him.

33:37.398 --> 33:40.607
Is it true that you said

33:40.773 --> 33:44.273
that you had seen Lucas' willie?

33:59.232 --> 34:02.482
Try to tell me what Lucas did.

34:02.648 --> 34:06.023
Tell me about that, Klara.

34:08.482 --> 34:13.357
- I'd like to go out and play.
- You just have to answer.

34:13.482 --> 34:17.773
Don't be afraid.
Ole won't hurt you.

34:17.898 --> 34:20.607
He just wants to know
what's happened.

34:24.357 --> 34:27.982
Did he show you his willie
here in the nursery?

34:30.773 --> 34:33.523
Did he, Klara?

34:38.523 --> 34:40.023
Klara?

34:53.732 --> 34:57.023
You are nodding.

34:57.148 --> 34:59.523
So it was here in nursery?

35:04.023 --> 35:08.148
Tell me what happened, then.

35:10.190 --> 35:13.815
Grethe said that
you said it was pointing.

35:15.440 --> 35:18.482
Was his willie pointing?

35:20.440 --> 35:23.898
I think so. I don't remember.

35:24.023 --> 35:26.440
So he showed you his willie?

35:34.232 --> 35:37.482
Is this uncomfortable to talk about?

35:48.523 --> 35:52.690
Is that because you don't like
what he did?

35:55.732 --> 36:01.273
Klara, you're doing a great job
answering my questions.

36:02.357 --> 36:05.065
We'll be done soon.

36:07.857 --> 36:12.982
What did he do
after he showed you his willie?

36:13.107 --> 36:15.398
I don't really know.

36:17.273 --> 36:19.107
Did you touch it?

36:25.107 --> 36:26.857
Do you remember?

36:28.315 --> 36:29.940
Did...

36:31.648 --> 36:34.857
...something white
come out of it?

36:42.482 --> 36:45.982
Perhaps this is too much at once.

36:46.107 --> 36:49.690
You can go back out and play.

36:49.815 --> 36:54.190
- Really?
- We just need to keep an eye on her.

37:01.440 --> 37:06.648
You and I know each other,
which is fine,

37:06.773 --> 37:12.065
but this is actually a matter
for the police.

37:12.232 --> 37:16.065
And we need the consent
of her parents.

37:16.190 --> 37:20.107
I appreciate your help.
I'm not sure how to handle it.

37:21.273 --> 37:25.107
Klara has a vivid imagination.

37:25.232 --> 37:28.232
But it doesn't seem to be the case.

37:29.107 --> 37:32.148
No, it doesn't appear that way.

37:33.357 --> 37:35.148
No.

37:43.523 --> 37:48.482
Ole says that we have to report it.

37:48.607 --> 37:50.898
We have to notify the authorities.

37:55.857 --> 38:00.357
- The parents' meeting is off, then.
- I don't think so.

