I'm Erik. This bastard is Elias.

01:13:31.732 --> 01:13:37.315
- Sit down. Get him some water.
- Are you thirsty?

01:13:40.482 --> 01:13:43.940
- Is tap water okay?
- Thanks.

01:13:44.065 --> 01:13:47.023
I've spoken to your mum.

01:13:47.148 --> 01:13:50.148
Remember to phone home.
Agreed?

01:13:54.523 --> 01:13:56.732
Do you know
what's happening to Dad?

01:14:02.440 --> 01:14:05.190
What did dad say?

01:14:05.315 --> 01:14:11.607
He said that Lucas has
a preliminary hearing tomorrow.

01:14:11.732 --> 01:14:15.315
At 8:30am.
There are two possible outcomes.

01:14:15.440 --> 01:14:20.107
Either the judge
confirms the remand.

01:14:20.232 --> 01:14:25.565
Or he finds no basis
for keeping him.

01:14:29.982 --> 01:14:32.607
What do you think will happen?

01:14:35.398 --> 01:14:37.232
I don't know.

01:14:38.232 --> 01:14:43.315
Apparently, all the children
are telling the same story.

01:14:44.190 --> 01:14:51.232
They describe your basement,
the wallpaper, the colour of the sofa.

01:14:52.732 --> 01:14:56.065
But when the police searched
your house this morning,

01:14:57.482 --> 01:14:59.523
they discovered what, Marcus?

01:15:04.732 --> 01:15:07.940
- That we don't have a basement.
- Exactly.

01:15:09.190 --> 01:15:13.065
- What does that mean?
- That they don't have a basement!

01:15:13.190 --> 01:15:18.690
- What does it mean for Lucas?
- It means there's still hope.

01:15:18.815 --> 01:15:25.190
It's common for children
to describe non-existing details.

01:15:25.315 --> 01:15:29.357
I don't know
if it's their imagination,

01:15:29.482 --> 01:15:33.523
or they pick it up from each other
or from their parents.

01:15:33.648 --> 01:15:36.732
It's always assumed
that children tell the truth.

01:15:38.398 --> 01:15:41.065
And unfortunately,
very often they do.

01:15:44.148 --> 01:15:49.065
- Now what?
- We'll have to wait and see.

01:15:50.523 --> 01:15:53.815
They'll call us tomorrow.

01:17:05.357 --> 01:17:07.732
Good morning, lad.

01:17:10.773 --> 01:17:12.565
Sleep well?

01:17:14.148 --> 01:17:16.815
I've brought you bread,
cheese and coffee.

01:17:16.940 --> 01:17:18.232
Thanks.

01:17:19.607 --> 01:17:22.482
I need to talk to you.

01:17:24.190 --> 01:17:29.732
I'm your godfather,
and you can count on me.

01:17:32.023 --> 01:17:34.565
No matter what happens. Okay?

01:17:38.690 --> 01:17:43.357
I've just spoken to your dad.
It looks good.

01:17:43.482 --> 01:17:46.732
- He's on his way in a taxi.
- What?

01:17:46.857 --> 01:17:48.815
They let him go.

01:17:48.940 --> 01:17:51.940
Eat your bread
and drink your coffee.

01:17:52.065 --> 01:17:57.023
Then we'll go downstairs
and welcome your dad.

01:18:22.315 --> 01:18:27.148
Hey! If you fondle your kid,
you'll go back to jail.

01:18:27.273 --> 01:18:29.982
We've got bacon and eggs.
It won't eat itself.

01:18:30.107 --> 01:18:33.273
- Come on.
- It's good to see you.

01:18:35.315 --> 01:18:38.023
Fanny! Hi, Fanny-girl.

01:18:38.148 --> 01:18:44.440
It's not too messy. You two,
grab a shovel and dig a basement.

01:18:44.565 --> 01:18:49.190
- Fanny has peed on the floor.
- No. It's probably the police.

01:19:19.565 --> 01:19:23.023
- Fanny!
- She'll be here in a minute.

01:19:31.107 --> 01:19:34.773
Do you want me to wash
the knickers I found?

01:19:38.315 --> 01:19:42.815
- Do you?
- What's your point?

01:19:42.940 --> 01:19:47.148
Nothing. I just asked
if you want them washed.

01:19:47.273 --> 01:19:50.940
- Yes, if you can find them.
- I will, in a minute.

01:19:52.273 --> 01:19:56.523
If you put them in the wash.
Are you seeing each other?

01:19:56.648 --> 01:19:59.232
I thought so.
Then all this happened.

01:20:02.357 --> 01:20:05.232
I wanted you to meet her,
but we'll see.

01:20:08.357 --> 01:20:13.523
- Do you have a girlfriend?
- No, it's not my thing.

01:20:15.440 --> 01:20:18.898
- Having a girlfriend?
- No.

01:20:22.648 --> 01:20:26.648
- I remember Jasmin.
- That's more than a year ago.

01:20:36.148 --> 01:20:39.065
Stay down. Don't move.

01:20:50.148 --> 01:20:52.357
Hello!

01:21:00.148 --> 01:21:01.565
Hello!

01:21:41.398 --> 01:21:43.315
What's that?

01:21:45.440 --> 01:21:47.940
- Dad, what is it?
- Go back in, Marcus.

01:21:51.607 --> 01:21:53.232
Let's go back in.

01:21:54.940 --> 01:21:59.023
- Come on in.
- Forget it, man.

01:22:23.815 --> 01:22:27.898
- You're dead!
- Stop it.

01:22:28.023 --> 01:22:31.398
- Relax...
- Fucking dead! Let go of me!

01:22:31.523 --> 01:22:34.440
- Stop it!
- I'll kill you!

01:22:37.898 --> 01:22:42.065
I'll kill you!
Bring her in. She's cold.

01:22:56.732 --> 01:22:58.190
Lucas?

01:23:08.648 --> 01:23:11.482
I'd like to be alone.

01:23:11.607 --> 01:23:13.690
Where's Marcus?

01:23:16.273 --> 01:23:19.523
- You sent him back to his mum?
- Yes.

01:23:23.315 --> 01:23:28.857
- Please leave, Bruun.
- Come on in.

01:23:28.982 --> 01:23:31.607
Go home, when I tell you to!

01:23:33.648 --> 01:23:35.398
Just go.

01:24:17.315 --> 01:24:20.857
- Here you go. Merry Christmas.
- Merry Christmas, Per.

01:24:22.690 --> 01:24:27.148
- I'd like two chops.
- We don't have chops.

01:24:30.940 --> 01:24:34.732
- Sorry, I mean those pork chops.
- You can't buy anything here.

01:24:43.523 --> 01:24:46.607
- I have a right to shop here.
- I want you to leave.

01:24:47.773 --> 01:24:52.273
- You need to leave. Scram.
- I want two chops.

01:25:06.065 --> 01:25:10.065
Off you go.
Don't come here.

01:25:15.440 --> 01:25:21.440
- You're not welcome.
- You can't hit a person like that.

01:25:21.565 --> 01:25:24.648
You have to leave now.

01:25:26.107 --> 01:25:29.107
- Is it normal to hit someone like that?
- Get out.

01:25:29.190 --> 01:25:31.690
I can walk!

01:25:37.857 --> 01:25:42.190
- I need my stuff.
- Get out! Now!

01:25:47.107 --> 01:25:51.857
- Get him out.
- Not a moment too soon.

01:25:52.023 --> 01:25:55.273
Get out!

01:25:55.398 --> 01:25:58.148
Thank you for coming.

01:26:00.857 --> 01:26:04.232
Get lost.

01:26:04.357 --> 01:26:07.482
Bugger off.
Don't come here ever again.

01:26:08.523 --> 01:26:10.273
Stay away.

01:27:01.857 --> 01:27:06.940
Didn't I tell you to get lost?
I won't tell you again.

01:27:08.732 --> 01:27:11.190
I just want to say something.

01:27:14.815 --> 01:27:19.357
- Fuck! Shit, that hurts.
- What the hell?

01:27:20.440 --> 01:27:24.857
- Can I have my things, please?
- Just give him his groceries.

01:27:30.065 --> 01:27:32.815
Fucking hell.

01:27:36.273 --> 01:27:38.607
That's 45.50.

01:27:49.065 --> 01:27:51.815
Good God, it's Lucas.

01:27:51.898 --> 01:27:54.398
Look at him. He's a mess.

01:27:59.982 --> 01:28:04.982
- I'll go and speak to him.
- Let's stay here until he's gone.

01:28:11.315 --> 01:28:13.357
Where's Fanny?

01:28:17.732 --> 01:28:19.648
I don't know.

01:28:21.523 --> 01:28:23.190
Shit...

01:28:52.940 --> 01:28:58.398
CHRISTMAS EVE

01:31:00.232 --> 01:31:02.815
I'd like to go in.

01:31:43.732 --> 01:31:48.523
A warm welcome to you all.
And merry Christmas.

01:31:48.648 --> 01:31:52.982
This is our Christmas service.

01:31:53.107 --> 01:31:56.523
As always,
we'll open with a prayer.

01:32:03.315 --> 01:32:07.523
I have come into this your house
to hear what you say to me,

01:32:07.648 --> 01:32:11.065
God the Father, you, Lord Jesus,

01:32:11.190 --> 01:32:15.982
good Holy Spirit,
in life and death my comforter.

01:32:16.815 --> 01:32:22.190
Open my heart by your Holy Spirit,
for the sake of Jesus Christ.

01:32:22.315 --> 01:32:27.482
So that I may learn to repent my sins
and to believe in Jesus,

01:32:27.607 --> 01:32:32.065
and every day
to grow in holy life and living.

01:32:32.190 --> 01:32:37.232
Hear me and grant this, O God,
through Jesus Christ. Amen.

01:32:43.482 --> 01:32:48.523
Christmas Eve is about Baby Jesus.

01:32:48.690 --> 01:32:51.732
The son of God is born.

01:32:51.857 --> 01:32:55.982
- What's wrong?
- I can tell by looking at him.

01:32:57.523 --> 01:32:59.357
Tell what?

01:33:00.982 --> 01:33:06.398
We should think about it
during the Lord's Prayer.

01:33:07.565 --> 01:33:13.982
Father, you say. And then it happens.
You have become a child of God.

01:33:15.315 --> 01:33:21.523
It is starting now.
Christmas time is a time for children.

01:33:22.648 --> 01:33:26.940
This year we want to emphasize
the gospel for Christmas Day.

01:33:27.065 --> 01:33:32.023
We've invited the nursery choir
who have been practising,

01:33:32.148 --> 01:33:37.773
so we may enjoy the hymn
"A Child is Born in Bethlehem".

01:33:44.982 --> 01:33:47.940
Come on, stand over here.

01:33:55.190 --> 01:33:57.815
Klara, you stand here.

01:34:00.148 --> 01:34:02.065
Take a step forward.

01:35:19.982 --> 01:35:24.107
What are you saying?

01:35:24.232 --> 01:35:28.773
- Have you got something to say to me?
- Stop it, Lucas.

01:35:28.898 --> 01:35:32.690
- You want to tell me something?
- Relax, Lucas!

01:35:32.815 --> 01:35:36.898
The whole town is listening.
Tell me!

01:35:37.023 --> 01:35:42.648
- You psycho!
- What do you want to say?

01:35:47.065 --> 01:35:52.107
- Stop it, you fucking psychopath!
- I want a word with Theo.

01:35:52.232 --> 01:35:57.482
Look into my eyes.
Look me in the eyes.

01:35:59.190 --> 01:36:03.732
What do you see?
Do you see anything?

01:36:05.065 --> 01:36:09.023
Nothing. There's nothing.

01:36:10.523 --> 01:36:12.065
There's nothing.

01:36:13.773 --> 01:36:15.898
You leave me alone now.

01:36:17.023 --> 01:36:22.065
Leave me alone now, Theo.
Then I'll go. Thank you.

01:36:48.482 --> 01:36:53.815
- You're the lucky one.
- You've had enough presents.

01:36:55.065 --> 01:36:58.315
It's exactly what you wished for.

01:37:01.190 --> 01:37:03.482
I've got her.

01:37:35.982 --> 01:37:37.773
Fanny...

01:37:51.482 --> 01:37:56.190
Lucas... Hi, Lucas.

01:38:06.648 --> 01:38:09.815
It was not supposed to happen.

01:38:22.940 --> 01:38:24.607
Klara, honey...

01:38:28.440 --> 01:38:30.815
It's not Lucas. It's just Dad.

01:38:39.273 --> 01:38:41.898
- Dad, are you crying?
- No.

01:38:43.648 --> 01:38:49.107
The world is full of evil.

01:38:50.190 --> 01:38:54.607
But if we hold on to each other,
it goes away.

01:38:55.940 --> 01:38:58.773
Are you really sad?

01:39:03.357 --> 01:39:05.148
No.

01:39:06.357 --> 01:39:08.940
You know,

01:39:09.065 --> 01:39:14.732
that Lucas is my very best friend.

01:39:14.857 --> 01:39:20.273
We rode our mopeds...

01:39:20.398 --> 01:39:23.482
We stole apples and all that.
I've told you before.

01:39:25.398 --> 01:39:28.273
I just said something foolish.

01:39:31.232 --> 01:39:33.440
He didn't do anything.

01:39:41.773 --> 01:39:44.982
- No.
- No.

01:39:48.398 --> 01:39:50.773
Go to sleep.

01:40:08.273 --> 01:40:11.815
- What are you doing?
- Just go join the others.

01:40:14.607 --> 01:40:16.607
Who's that for?

01:40:17.773 --> 01:40:21.523
Give me ten minutes,
and I'll be back.

01:40:22.982 --> 01:40:27.148
Theo.
You're not going to his place.

01:40:29.898 --> 01:40:33.857
Agnes, step aside.

01:40:58.690 --> 01:41:03.357
- Hey. Lucas...
- What are you doing here?

01:41:03.482 --> 01:41:05.190
It's just me.

01:41:12.023 --> 01:41:14.523
What the hell are you doing here?

01:41:22.315 --> 01:41:25.398
I brought you some food,
in case...

01:41:30.607 --> 01:41:32.690
Are you hungry?

01:41:39.565 --> 01:41:42.773
Go ahead and eat, if you want.

01:42:47.648 --> 01:42:52.482
It's very nice.
You can just go home, if you like.

01:42:59.690 --> 01:43:01.190
No...

01:43:02.773 --> 01:43:06.398
Actually,
I'd like to stay for a while.

01:43:06.523 --> 01:43:08.315
If it's okay.

01:44:07.982 --> 01:44:12.440
ONE YEAR LATER

01:44:35.773 --> 01:44:37.857
- Ready?
- Yes.

01:44:41.523 --> 01:44:43.273
- Hi, Johan.
- Hello.

01:44:50.315 --> 01:44:52.648
Hi, Dan. So we're back.

01:44:53.690 --> 01:44:55.357
Lucas!

01:44:57.940 --> 01:45:00.898
- Good to see you.
- You too.

01:45:05.523 --> 01:45:11.482
Quiet! Shut up.
We're gathered here for a reason.

01:45:12.273 --> 01:45:16.232
This is the day
when boys become men,

01:45:16.357 --> 01:45:18.440
and men become boys.

01:45:18.565 --> 01:45:23.315
Marcus, old boy.
You have your hunting licence.

01:45:23.440 --> 01:45:27.357
And it's your turn
tomorrow at the crack of dawn.

01:45:28.440 --> 01:45:31.398
You're becoming an adult.

01:45:31.523 --> 01:45:34.732
You're about to conquer the forest.

01:45:34.857 --> 01:45:36.773
Come here, my boy.

01:45:46.523 --> 01:45:49.940
It's a great pleasure
to see you here.

01:45:51.482 --> 01:45:53.982
This is for you.

01:46:08.815 --> 01:46:11.815
I wish you were my boy,

01:46:11.940 --> 01:46:15.982
and that this was
a present from me.

01:46:16.065 --> 01:46:22.398
But it's not from me.
It's from your father.

01:46:22.523 --> 01:46:25.898
It's been in your family
for generations,

01:46:26.023 --> 01:46:29.398
and now...it's yours.

01:46:30.607 --> 01:46:32.232
Take care of it.

01:46:32.357 --> 01:46:37.357
Your grandfather missed
many deer

01:46:37.482 --> 01:46:39.773
in order to feed your family.

01:46:39.940 --> 01:46:43.523
Don't forget that.
Congratulations!

01:46:44.815 --> 01:46:49.065
<i>We hope that he will drink with us,
and drink with us, and drink with us!</i>

01:46:49.190 --> 01:46:53.232
<i>We hope that he will drink with us,
that he will drink with us!</i>

01:46:53.357 --> 01:46:58.398
<i>That he will drink with us!</i>

01:46:58.523 --> 01:46:59.940
Cheers and congratulations!

01:47:00.065 --> 01:47:02.523
Lunch is served!

01:47:07.523 --> 01:47:11.107
- Do you have any more?
- We'll bring it in.

01:47:30.648 --> 01:47:35.482
That's tricky. Look at all
those lines you can't step on.

01:47:35.607 --> 01:47:38.357
Yes, I was just
thinking the same.

01:47:41.107 --> 01:47:43.482
- Hi, Klara.

01:47:45.107 --> 01:47:46.940
Are you okay?

01:47:59.357 --> 01:48:04.982
- How do we get around those lines?
- I don't know. There are so many.

01:48:05.107 --> 01:48:06.732
Yes.

01:48:15.232 --> 01:48:16.440
Come.

01:48:22.857 --> 01:48:24.273
Careful now.

01:48:25.607 --> 01:48:29.648
Very long steps...

01:48:30.565 --> 01:48:34.440
We made it.
I think your dad is in there.

01:48:37.648 --> 01:48:39.482
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

01:48:56.607 --> 01:49:01.357
- You're scaring the deer.
- What am I doing?

01:49:03.773 --> 01:49:07.148
- Did I ruin everything?
- No, it'll be back.

01:49:07.857 --> 01:49:13.523
Marcus. Go wait by your deer stand.
You'll wait a while but they'll come.

01:49:15.523 --> 01:49:17.440
Are you ready?
